Chavez Says Ahmadinejad Asked to Re-Start Libya Peace Efforts

-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 
2011-04-17T23:45:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/chavez-says-ahmadinejad-asked-to-re-start-libya-peace-efforts.html
Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez ,
speaking on state television, said Iranian President  Mahmoud Ahmadinejad  asked him in a telephone conversation to re-activate
his proposal to negotiate peace in  Libya .  Chavez said his government would work with the  African
Union  on expanding a peace commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Orozco in Caracas at 
 jorozco8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
